<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-211-063 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 495 326</DOCID><JOURNAL>The LocalNetter  March 1991 v11 n3 p34(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Architecture Technology Corp. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Gandalf 10Base-T wiring hubs. (Access Hub 12, 48 and 132)(International News) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Gandalf Data Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Gandalf Technologies Access Hub 12 (Network hub) (Productintroduction)Gandalf Technologies Access Hub 48 (Network hub) (Productintroduction)Gandalf Technologies Access Hub 132 (Network hub) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product Introduction10BaseTConcentratorsNetwork Hubs.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Gandalf Data has recently introduced a series of 10BASE-T compliantintelligent wiring hubs which allow users to establish 802.3 Ethernetnetworks with unshielded-twisted pair wiring.andM;Called the Access Hub series, the Gandalf 10BASE-T wiring concentrators aredesigned to meet the local-area network (LAN) connectivity needs of a widerange of user communities, from small workgroups to entire organizations.andM;Three Access Hub configurations are available.andP;  The Access Hub 12 provides10BASE-T connectivity for up to 12 LAN devices and one access unit interface(AUI) connection.andP;  The intelligent Access Hub 48 and Access Hub 132 aremodular and accommodate up to 48 and 132 LAN devices, respectively.andP;  They canbe configured with a variety of modules to provide unshielded-twisted-pair,fiber-optic, and thick or thin coaxial ports.andM;Access Hub concentrators can be networked together and connected to LANs ofvarious media types to create a single.andP;  centrally managed enterprise-wideLAN.andM;The Access Hub series supports SNMP and also complies with emerging OSInetwork management standards, providing a smooth migration path.andP;  Inaddition, Gandalf's UNIX-based Access Manager network management systemoffers a graphical user interface and fault management.andP;  Access Hubconcentrators are available for immediate delivery.andP;  The price for Access Hub12 is $1,295.andP;  Access Hub 48 and Access Hub 132 system prices begin at lessthan $200 per port.andM;Customer inquiries may be directed to Barbara Allen at 1-800-GANDALF1-800-426-3253).andO;</TEXT></DOC>